{"parse":{"title":"Tax amortization benefit","pageid":37898951,"revid":845800694,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>In <a href=\"/wiki/Accounting\" title=\"Accounting\">accounting</a>, <b>tax amortization benefit</b> (or <b>tax amortisation benefit</b>) refers to the <a href=\"/wiki/Present_value\" title=\"Present value\">present value</a> of income tax savings resulting from the <a href=\"/wiki/Tax_deduction\" title=\"Tax deduction\">tax deduction</a> generated by the <a href=\"/wiki/Amortization\" title=\"Amortization\">amortization</a> of an <a href=\"/wiki/Intangible_asset\" title=\"Intangible asset\">intangible asset</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Intangible_asset_valuation\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Intangible asset valuation</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Circularity_of_the_tax_amortization_benefit\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Circularity of the tax amortization benefit</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Tax_amortization_benefit_factor\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Tax amortization benefit factor</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Sources\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Sources</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">7</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Intangible_asset_valuation\">Intangible asset valuation</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Tax_amortization_benefit&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Intangible asset valuation\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>When the purchaser of an intangible asset is allowed to amortize the price of the asset as an expense for tax purposes, the value of the asset is enhanced by this tax amortization benefit.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Specifically, the <a href=\"/wiki/Fair_market_value\" title=\"Fair market value\">fair market value</a> of the asset is increased by the present value of the future tax savings derived from the tax amortization of the asset. The present value of these savings is to be estimated and included as a part of the fair market value when valuing an intangible asset.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Circularity_of_the_tax_amortization_benefit\">Circularity of the tax amortization benefit</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Tax_amortization_benefit&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Circularity of the tax amortization benefit\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The present value of the future tax savings is a mathematical function of the fair market value.  This creates circularity, because the fair market value includes the present value of the tax savings.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> This circularity can be handled using a two-step procedure consisting in estimating the value of the intangible asset in the absence of the tax amortization benefit first and then grossing up the previous value by a tax amortization benefit factor.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<dl><dd><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle FMV\\,=\\,{VBAB*TAB_{factor}}}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mi>M</mi>\n        <mi>V</mi>\n        <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\" />\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\" />\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mi>V</mi>\n          <mi>B</mi>\n          <mi>A</mi>\n          <mi>B</mi>\n          <mo>&#x2217;<!-- \u2217 --></mo>\n          <mi>T</mi>\n          <mi>A</mi>\n          <msub>\n            <mi>B</mi>\n            <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n              <mi>f</mi>\n              <mi>a</mi>\n              <mi>c</mi>\n              <mi>t</mi>\n              <mi>o</mi>\n              <mi>r</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </msub>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle FMV\\,=\\,{VBAB*TAB_{factor}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/5371f39f7b734e329f1411e6ea9c553edc0f7a45\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -1.005ex; width:29.09ex; height:2.843ex;\" alt=\"{\\displaystyle FMV\\,=\\,{VBAB*TAB_{factor}}}\"/></span></dd></dl>\n<p>where\n</p>\n<ol><li>FMV is the fair market value of the intangible asset</li>\n<li>VBAB is the value of the intangible asset before amortization benefits</li>\n<li>TAB factor is the result of the formula defined below</li></ol>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Tax_amortization_benefit_factor\">Tax amortization benefit factor</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Tax_amortization_benefit&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Tax amortization benefit factor\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The tax amortization benefit factor (or TAB factor) is the result of a mathematical function of a <a href=\"/wiki/Corporate_tax\" title=\"Corporate tax\">corporate tax</a> rate, a <a href=\"/wiki/Discount_window\" title=\"Discount window\">discount rate</a> and a tax amortization period:\n</p>\n<dl><dd><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle TAB_{factor}\\,=\\,{1 \\over [1-{t \\over n}*({1 \\over k}-{1 \\over (k*(1+k)^{n})})]}}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mi>T</mi>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>B</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi>f</mi>\n            <mi>a</mi>\n            <mi>c</mi>\n            <mi>t</mi>\n            <mi>o</mi>\n            <mi>r</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\" />\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\" />\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo stretchy=\"false\">[</mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \u2212 --></mo>\n              <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                <mfrac>\n                  <mi>t</mi>\n                  <mi>n</mi>\n                </mfrac>\n              </mrow>\n              <mo>&#x2217;<!-- \u2217 --></mo>\n              <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n              <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                <mfrac>\n                  <mn>1</mn>\n                  <mi>k</mi>\n                </mfrac>\n              </mrow>\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \u2212 --></mo>\n              <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                <mfrac>\n                  <mn>1</mn>\n                  <mrow>\n                    <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n                    <mi>k</mi>\n                    <mo>&#x2217;<!-- \u2217 --></mo>\n                    <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n                    <mn>1</mn>\n                    <mo>+</mo>\n                    <mi>k</mi>\n                    <msup>\n                      <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n                      <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                        <mi>n</mi>\n                      </mrow>\n                    </msup>\n                    <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n                  </mrow>\n                </mfrac>\n              </mrow>\n              <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n              <mo stretchy=\"false\">]</mo>\n            </mrow>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle TAB_{factor}\\,=\\,{1 \\over [1-{t \\over n}*({1 \\over k}-{1 \\over (k*(1+k)^{n})})]}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/d219390ecd9404312f6268cfc46d8ff37dffc526\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -4.005ex; width:39.354ex; height:7.343ex;\" alt=\"{\\displaystyle TAB_{factor}\\,=\\,{1 \\over [1-{t \\over n}*({1 \\over k}-{1 \\over (k*(1+k)^{n})})]}}\"/></span></dd></dl>\n<p>where\n</p>\n<ol><li>TAB factor is the value assuming end-year discounting</li>\n<li>t is the corporate tax rate applicable to the future amortization of the asset</li>\n<li>n is the tax amortization period of the asset in years</li>\n<li>k is the discount rate</li></ol>\n<p>The corporate tax rate as well as the tax amortization period are defined by country-specific tax legislations. The tax amortization period might be different from the useful life used in accounting. For example, while <a href=\"/wiki/Trademarks\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Trademarks\">trademarks</a> can have an indefinite useful life for accounting purposes, the tax legislation of the <a href=\"/wiki/United_States\" title=\"United States\">United States</a> establishes a mandatory 15-year amortization period for trademarks.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Tax_amortization_benefit&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Business_valuation\" title=\"Business valuation\">Business valuation</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Business_valuation_standard\" title=\"Business valuation standard\">Business valuation standard</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Intellectual_property_valuation\" title=\"Intellectual property valuation\">Intellectual property valuation</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Market-based_valuation\" title=\"Market-based valuation\">Market-based valuation</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Purchase_price_allocation\" title=\"Purchase price allocation\">Purchase price allocation</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Tax_amortization_benefit&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.iasplus.com/en/binary/ivsc/0708intangibleassetsdp.pdf#page=27\">See paragraph 5.25 of International Valuation Standards Committee. Determination of Fair Value of Intangible Assets for IFRS Reporting Purposes. 2007.</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.amortizationtables.ca/NC3.pdf\">Deloitte. Fair Value, Intangible and Purchase Price Allocation. 2011</a><sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template\"><span style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">&#91;<i><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Link_rot\" title=\"Wikipedia:Link rot\"><span title=\"&#160;Dead link since June 2018\">permanent dead link</span></a></i>&#93;</span></sup></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.taxamortisation.com/theoretical-background.html\">See section \"Calculating the TAB\" section about two-step procedure to solve the circularity issue</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.irs.gov/Businesses/Partnerships/Partnership---Audit-Technique-Guide---Chapter-3---Contribution-of-Property-with-Built-in-Gain-or-Loss---IRC-section-704(c)-(Revised-12-2007)#13\">IRC SECTION 704(c) AND IRC SECTION 197 INTANGIBLES</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Sources\">Sources</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Tax_amortization_benefit&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: Sources\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>The Canadian Institute of Chartered Business Valuators. <i>Illustrative Example of Intangible Asset Valuation</i>. 2009.</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Tax_amortization_benefit&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.taxamortisation.com/online-tab-calculator.html\">Online tax amortization benefit calculator and a list of legal tax amortization periods per country</a></li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.fxsolver.com/solve/share/eQH7t9jmUu2XFcpMJQDXiQ==/\">Tax amortization benefit calculator</a></li></ul>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw1264\nCached time: 20180911124724\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.072 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.165 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 266/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 2204/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 629/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 12/40\nExpensive parser function count: 1/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 2068/5000000 bytes\nNumber of Wikibase entities loaded: 0/400\nLua time usage: 0.019/10.000 seconds\nLua memory usage: 826 KB/50 MB\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   74.168      1 Template:Reflist\n100.00%   74.168      1 -total\n 73.46%   54.485      1 Template:Dead_link\n 47.43%   35.177      1 Template:Fix\n 42.41%   31.45